### End-to-End Tests

<!-- {{#if tauri}} -->
#### TC-E001: Desktop App Launch

**Scenario**: User opens desktop app

**Test**:
```typescript
test('app launches and shows main window', async () => {
  const app = await startApp();

  // Wait for window
  await app.client.waitForExist('#main-window', { timeout: 5000 });

  // Verify UI elements
  const title = await app.client.getText('#app-title');
  expect(title).toBe('{{projectName}}');

  await app.stop();
});
```

#### TC-E002: Create and Save Data

**Scenario**: User creates and saves data offline

**Test**:
```typescript
test('user can create data offline', async () => {
  const app = await startApp();

  // Navigate to create form
  await app.client.click('#new-post-button');

  // Fill form
  await app.client.setValue('#title-input', 'Test Post');
  await app.client.setValue('#content-input', 'Test content...');

  // Save
  await app.client.click('#save-button');

  // Verify saved
  await app.client.waitForText('Saved successfully', { timeout: 2000 });

  // Verify in database
  const posts = await app.getLocalData('posts');
  expect(posts).toHaveLength(1);
  expect(posts[0].title).toBe('Test Post');

  await app.stop();
});
```
<!-- {{/if}} -->

